When(/^I navigate to "([^"]*)" using the left nav$/) do |opt|
  @browser.goto("#{@browser.url}#")
  on(PolicyManagementPage) do |page|
    page.toggle_side_navbar
    page.left_nav.navigate_to(opt)
  rescue Exception => ex
    raise ex unless /divProcessingPageOverlay/.match?(ex.message)

    page.wait_for_processing_overlay_to_close
    page.toggle_side_navbar
    page.left_nav.navigate_to(opt)
  end
end

Then(/^the vehicle I added should be present in the vehicle grid$/) do
  on(AutoPolicySummaryPage) do |page|
    data = data_for 'vehicle_information_panel'
    vehicle = page.vehicle_info_panel.vehicles.last
    RSpec.capture_assertions do
      %w[year make model vin].each do |what|
        expect(vehicle.send(what).downcase).to eq(data["vehicle_#{what}"].downcase)
      end
    ensure
      page.wait_for_modal_masker
      # vehicle&.safe_delete
      # page.auto_general_info_modal.dismiss if page.auto_general_info_modal?
    end
  end

Then(/^I (should|should not) see the manual (other vehicle|vehicle|policy) coverage I added$/) do |should_or_not, vehicle_or_policy_coverage|
  @coverage = data_for('manual_coverage')
  on(AutoPolicySummaryPage) do |page|
    page.send("open_#{vehicle_or_policy_coverage.snakecase}_coverages")
    modal = vehicle_or_policy_coverage.include?('vehicle') ? page.auto_vehicle_coverages_modal : page.auto_policy_optional_coverages_modal
    whether_should = should_or_not == 'should'
    expect(modal.manual_coverages.first.description == @coverage['description']).to eq(whether_should)
    expect(modal.manual_coverages.first.premium == "$ #{@coverage['premium']}").to eq(whether_should)
  end
end

And(/^the coverages I entered display in the auto coverages panel$/) do
  on(AutoPolicySummaryPage) do |page|
    panel = page.policy_coverages_panel
    expected = data_for('expected_auto_policy_level_coverages')
    RSpec.capture_assertions do
      expected.keys.each do |which|
        next unless expected.key?(which.to_s)

        actual = panel.send(which)
        expect(actual).to eq(expected[which.to_s]), "Expected #{which} to be #{expected[which.to_s]} but it is #{actual}"
      end
    end
  end
end

And(/^I should see the following deductible options for the auto vehicle coverages$/) do |table|
  expected = {}
  table.rows.each { |r| expected[r[0]] ||= []; expected[r[0]] << r[1] }

  on(AutoPolicySummaryPage) do |page|
    modal = page.auto_vehicle_coverages_modal
    RSpec.capture_assertions do
      expected.each do |field, values|
        modal.coverage_list.select_coverage(field)
        deductibles = modal.deductible_element.options.map(&:text)
        deductibles.delete('--Select--')
        expect(deductibles).to eq(values)
      end
    end
  end
end

Then(/^the new (applicant|non-person applicant) should be displayed in the general information$/) do |type|
  on(AccountSummaryPage) do |page|
    found_applicant = page.applicants_panel.reverse_find_applicant_by_name(@added_applicant)
    begin
      expect(found_applicant).not_to be_nil, "Could not find #{@added_applicant.applicant_full_name} in the applicants list"
      expect(found_applicant.dob).to start_with(@added_applicant['date_of_birth']), "DOB does not match for #{@added_applicant.applicant_full_name}" if type == 'applicant'
      expect(found_applicant.phone).to start_with(@added_applicant.applicant_phone_with_type)
      expect(found_applicant.email).to eq(@added_applicant['emails'].join("\n"))
      expect(found_applicant.address.downcase).to start_with(@added_applicant.applicant_display_address.downcase)
      expect(found_applicant.is_contact?).to eq(@added_applicant['is_contact'].to_s.casecmp('yes').zero?)
    ensure
      found_applicant&.safe_delete
    end
  end
end

Given(/^I have created (\d+) new "([^"]*)" policies$/) do |count, type|
  @added_policies ||= []
  count.times do |time_index|
    STDOUT.puts "Starting Account #{time_index+1}/#{count}"
    visit(LoginPage).populate
    begin
      navigate_all(using: type.downcase.to_sym, visit: true)
    rescue Exception => ex
      # rubocop:disable Lint/Debugger
      binding.pry if Nenv.cuke_debug?
      # rubocop:enable Lint/Debugger
      puts ex.message
      raise ex
    end
    CleanupHelper.register_activity_for_deletion @browser.url
    act_id = @browser.url.split('=').last

    on(PolicyManagementPage) do |page|
      page.toggle_side_navbar
      page.left_nav.navigate_to('Account Summary')
    end

    pol_id = @browser.url.split('=').last
    @added_policies << { 'existing_account' => { 'id' => pol_id }, 'existing_auto_policy' => { 'id' => act_id } }
  end
end

      @driver_assignments << { vehicle: p.grid_key, driver: p.occasional_use_drivers.first.driver, use: 'Occasional' }

  end

  begin
